--- 
amount: 10
rows: 
- "scenario author: author_name"
- You can put "#SCRIPT NAME" in first row.
- Type any BASH commands in next rows.
- Press RUN button to execute only checked command. 
- Each command can run any process you need.
- One command can be splitted by rows.
- Put ';' in the end of string to divide seperate commands.
- Save inserted commands pressing SAVE button.
- Load existed scenario pressing LOAD button.
- You can adjust view selecting lines, boxes and fields.
- You can display up to 50 rows. Look examples.

